---
/**
 * FeaturesZigzag - Alternating left/right feature blocks
 * Each feature has text + code snippet or illustration
 */
---

<section class="features-section not-content">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 class="section-title">Built for the Quantum Era</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">Everything you need to deploy post-quantum PKI in production.</p>

    <!-- Feature 1: Post-Quantum Ready -->
    <div class="feature-row fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge">Core</span>
        <h3>Post-Quantum Ready</h3>
        <p>Native support for NIST post-quantum algorithms. ML-DSA for signatures, ML-KEM for key encapsulation, SLH-DSA for hash-based signatures. Fully FIPS 203/204/205 compliant.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Generate ML-DSA key pair</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki key generate \
    --algorithm <span class="h">ml-dsa-65</span> \
    --out root-ca.key

<span class="o">&#10003; ML-DSA-65 key pair generated</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 2: Hybrid Certificates (reversed) -->
    <div class="feature-row reversed fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge blue">Migration</span>
        <h3>Hybrid Certificates</h3>
        <p>Dual-algorithm certificates combine classical (RSA, ECDSA) with post-quantum algorithms. Backward compatible with existing infrastructure while quantum-safe.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Issue hybrid certificate</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki cert issue \
    --profile hybrid-server \
    --algorithm <span class="h">ml-dsa-65+ecdsa-p256</span> \
    --cn "api.example.com"

<span class="o">&#10003; Hybrid certificate issued</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 3: CLI-First -->
    <div class="feature-row fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge green">DevOps</span>
        <h3>CLI-First</h3>
        <p>Single binary, zero dependencies. Script everything. Works in CI/CD pipelines, containers, and air-gapped environments. Install in seconds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># One-line install</span>
<span class="p">$</span> brew install qentriq/tap/qpki

<span class="c"># Or download binary</span>
<span class="p">$</span> curl -sSL <span class="h">get.qpki.io</span> | sh

<span class="o">&#10003; qpki v1.0 ready</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 4: Battle-Tested (reversed) -->
    <div class="feature-row reversed fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge orange">Quality</span>
        <h3>Battle-Tested</h3>
        <p>Cross-validated with OpenSSL and BouncyCastle. Standards-compliant X.509 certificates. Full RFC compliance for OCSP, TSA, CRL, and CMS.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="compat-grid">
          <div class="compat-item">
            <span class="compat-check">&#10003;</span>
            <span>OpenSSL</span>
          </div>
          <div class="compat-item">
            <span class="compat-check">&#10003;</span>
            <span>BouncyCastle</span>
          </div>
          <div class="compat-item">
            <span class="compat-check">&#10003;</span>
            <span>X.509 v3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="compat-item">
            <span class="compat-check">&#10003;</span>
            <span>OCSP / CRL</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .features-section {
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-title {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    max-width: 550px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
  }

  .feature-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .feature-row:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .feature-row.reversed {
    direction: rtl;
  }

  .feature-row.reversed > * {
    direction: ltr;
  }

  .feature-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    background: rgba(255, 85, 163, 0.1);
    color: #FF55A3;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 85, 163, 0.2);
  }

  .feature-badge.blue {
    background: rgba(0, 91, 197, 0.1);
    color: #60a5fa;
    border-color: rgba(0, 91, 197, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.green {
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1);
    color: #22c55e;
    border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.orange {
    background: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.1);
    color: #eab308;
    border-color: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-text h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .feature-text p {
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* Mini terminal */
  .mini-terminal {
    background: #1a1d27;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .mini-header {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .dot-sm {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  .mini-terminal pre {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .mini-terminal code {
    font-family: var(--q-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    background: none !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
  }

  .mini-terminal .c { color: #64748b; }
  .mini-terminal .p { color: #FF55A3; }
  .mini-terminal .h { color: #FF55A3; font-weight: 600; }
  .mini-terminal .o { color: #22c55e; }

  /* Compat grid */
  .compat-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .compat-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .compat-item:hover {
    border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.3);
  }

  .compat-check {
    color: #22c55e;
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.25rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* Light mode */
  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border-color: #e2e8f0;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-header {
    background: #f1f5f9;
    border-bottom-color: #e2e8f0;
  }

  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal code {
    color: #1e293b;
  }

  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal .c { color: #94a3b8; }
  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal .p { color: #005BC5; }
  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal .h { color: #005BC5; }

  :root[data-theme='light'] .compat-item {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
    border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .feature-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .feature-row.reversed {
      direction: ltr;
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
